TI  - An Empirical Analysis and Extension of the Bartlett and Ghoshal Typology of Multinational Companies
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 101
EP  - 120
VL  - 31
IS  - 1
AB  - This study offers an empirical test and extension of the Bartlett and Ghoshal typology of multinational companies (MNCs) A three-fold typology of multinational companies: Global, Multidomestic and Transnational is developed from the literature. This typology is tested using data from 166 subsidiaries of 37 MNCs, headquartered in 9 different countries. Subsidiaries in the three types of MNCs are shown to differ significantly in aspects of interdependence and local responsiveness.
SN  - 1478-6990
